A Nairobi court has ordered investigations into allegations of assault meted to a woman who refused an officer's sexual advances at the Central police station. Mary Wanjiru told chief magistrate Francis Andayi that she was physically assaulted and locked up for three days by a police officer when she rejected his sexual overtures. The woman, who denied charges of assaulting the officer, said she had gone to the station on Saturday night to report an incident between her and her boyfriend. She told court that the officer allegedly asked her whether she could have sex with her before being assisted. And when she rejected, Wanjiru was allegedly beaten up and locked up in the cells for more than 24 hours. The court noted that she has visible injuries on her left thigh, buttocks, and a black eye. She also had a swollen leg. Click here for the latest political news 